FABULOUS and quite simple. 0ne of can of beans might be sufficient (particularly if that's you have on hand). I added 3 cloves of garlic and at least a tsp of dried thyme once the onions were done. After 20 mins I cranked the heat up to 400 degrees for 10 mins, then back down to 250 to hold until hubby was home - i think the extra time in the oven really helped the flavors meld. Also Farmland bacon is the BEST for cooking.

